Citations
Date: 0/0/1919
Source: Wool Grower
Author:
Vol / Page: 19
Edition:
Quote: Condition - refers to the state of a fleece, having regard to the amount of natural grease or yolk, moisture or earthy matter it contains. A full, bright, light Lincoln may be termed 'light' in condition. Heavy conditioned wool contains more than the required amount of grease for the preservation of the fleece.
